issuesFound.explanation:
The form uses inlineValidator which only adds error messages; it never toggles aria‑invalid, leaving AT users unaware of which fields are invalid.  
  Fix (inside the validation loop):  
  ```js
  const result = inlineValidator.validate(field);
  if (!result.valid) {
    setAttr(field, 'aria-invalid', 'true');   // ← add
  } else {
    setAttr(field, 'aria-invalid', 'false'); // ← add on success
  }
  ```

